Conclusion

This project successfully demonstrates the design and implementation of an optimal thermal control system using LQR and Kalman filtering.

The proposed LQG controller:

- Achieves superior stability
- Minimizes overshoot
- Reduces settling time
- Handles disturbances effectively

Compared to classical PID control, the LQG approach provides a more robust and efficient solution for modern engineering systems.

This work highlights the importance of model-based control techniques in advanced aerospace applications and serves as a foundation for further research in optimal and intelligent control systems.